abstract: >-
Structural Cognitive Emergence (SCE) is a structural intelligence framework
investigating how concepts, questions, curiosity, and autonomous inquiry may
emerge from growing cognitive structures. Starting from the Cat Problem —
why a child can form a concept from only a few examples — this repository
develops a structural account of differential concept formation, in-situ
knowledge growth, calling graph emergence, gap detection, why generation,
education as question preservation, autonomous AI, and cross-graph gap
emergence. The project proposes that questions are not stored linguistic
objects but triggered cognitive events arising from unresolved structural gaps.

